children.name: pickRay
children.comment:
On success, [rayNear] and [rayFar] are the points where
the screen space [pickX], [pickY] intersect with the near and far
planes respectively.

The viewport is specified by ([viewportX], [viewportWidth]) and
([viewportY], [viewportHeight]).

[cameraMatrix] includes both the projection and view transforms.

Returns false on error, for example, the mouse is not in the viewport

children.name: unproject
children.comment:
On success, Sets [pickWorld] to be the world space position of
the screen space [pickX], [pickY], and [pickZ].

The viewport is specified by ([viewportX], [viewportWidth]) and
([viewportY], [viewportHeight]).

[cameraMatrix] includes both the projection and view transforms.

[pickZ] is typically either 0.0 (near plane) or 1.0 (far plane).

Returns false on error, for example, the mouse is not in the viewport

children.name: makePlaneReflection

Returns a transformation matrix that transforms points by reflecting
them through the plane specified with [planeNormal] and [planePoint]

children.name: makePlaneProjection
children.comment:
Returns a transformation matrix that transforms points onto
the plane specified with [planeNormal] and [planePoint]

children.name: makeLookAt
children.comment:
Returns an OpenGL look at matrix.
The camera is located at [cameraPosition] and is focused
on [cameraFocusPostion].

The [upDirection] is almost always (0, 1, 0).

children.name: copyFromArray
children.comment: Copies elements from [array] into [this] starting at [offset].

children.name: length
children.comment: Returns length of this

children.name: length2
children.comment: Returns squared length of this

children.name: isInfinite
children.comment: Returns true if any component is infinite.

children.name: isNaN
children.comment: Returns true if any component is NaN.

children.name: vec2
children.comment: Constructs a new [vec2]. Follows GLSL constructor syntax so many combinations are possible

children.name: vec2.zero
children.comment: Constructs a new [vec2] zero vector.

children.name: vec2.copy
children.comment: Constructs a copy of [other].

children.name: vec2.raw
children.comment: Constructs a new [vec2] that is initialized with passed in values.

children.name: vec2.array
children.comment: Constructs a new [vec2] that is initialized with values from [array] starting at [offset].
